        <section id="update-minecraft">

            <h2>How to Update Minecraft</h2>

            <p>Keeping your Minecraft game up to date is important to ensure you have access to the latest features and bug fixes. Follow these steps to update Minecraft:</p>

            <ol>

                <li>

                    <h3>Check for Updates</h3>

                    <p>Open the Minecraft launcher and click on the "Options" button.</p>

                    <img src="launcher-options.png" alt="Minecraft launcher options">

                </li>

                <li>

                    <h3>Click on "Check for Updates"</h3>

                    <p>In the options menu, click on the "Check for Updates" button.</p>

                    <img src="check-for-updates.png" alt="Check for updates button">

                </li>

                <li>

                    <h3>Download the Update</h3>

                    <p>If an update is available, click on the "Download" button to download the update.</p>

                    <img src="download-update.png" alt="Download update button">

                </li>

                <li>

                    <h3>Wait for the Update to Install</h3>

                    <p>Wait for the update to download and install. This may take a few minutes.</p>

                    <img src="update-installing.png" alt="Update installing">

                </li>

                <li>

                    <h3>Launch Minecraft</h3>

                    <p>Once the update is installed, click on the "Play" button to launch Minecraft.</p>

                    <img src="launch-minecraft.png" alt="Launch Minecraft button">

                </li>

            </ol>

            <p>That's it! You should now be running the latest version of Minecraft.</p>

        </section>

    </main>

