        <section id="create-server">

            <h2>How to Make a Minecraft Server</h2>

            <p>Creating a Minecraft server allows you to play with friends and family online. Follow these steps to set up your own Minecraft server:</p>

            <ol>

                <li>

                    <h3>Download the Minecraft Server Software</h3>

                    <p>Download the Minecraft server software from the official Minecraft website.</p>

                    <a href="https://www.minecraft.net/en/download/server">Download Now</a>

                </li>

                <li>

                    <h3>Create a New Folder for Your Server</h3>

                    <p>Create a new folder on your computer to store your Minecraft server files.</p>

                    <img src="create-folder.png" alt="Create a new folder">

                </li>

                <li>

                    <h3>Extract the Server Software</h3>

                    <p>Extract the Minecraft server software to the new folder you created.</p>

                    <img src="extract-software.png" alt="Extract the server software">

                </li>

                <li>

                    <h3>Configure Your Server</h3>

                    <p>Edit the `server.properties` file to configure your server settings.</p>

                    <code>server.properties</code>

                    <pre>

server-name=My Minecraft Server

gamemode=survival

difficulty=normal

max-players=20

                    </pre>

                </li>

                <li>

                    <h3>Start Your Server</h3>

                    <p>Run the `start.bat` file (on Windows) or `start.sh` file (on Mac/Linux) to start your Minecraft server.</p>

                    <img src="start-server.png" alt="Start your server">

                </li>

                <li>

                    <h3>Connect to Your Server</h3>

                    <p>Open Minecraft and connect to your server by entering the server address and port number.</p>

                    <img src="connect-server.png" alt="Connect to your server">

                </li>

            </ol>

            <p>That's it! You now have a Minecraft server up and running. Invite your friends to join and start playing together.</p>

        </section>

    </main>

</body>

</html>
